Reasoning: The paper focuses on the development of a new method for transducing a third dimension to the sensor data via Voronoi tessellation, which can be used to infer key tactile features such as tip displacement, contact location, shear direction and magnitude. The paper also discusses the use of these methods in complex systems such as robot hands. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of AI techniques for inference, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the application of these methods in unstructured and unknown environments, which makes cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category as well.
